import itertools
import math
a = int(input())
for _ in range(a):
    b = int(input())
    so =[str(i) for i in range(1,b+1)]
    hoan_vi = list(itertools.permutations(so))
    hoan_vi.sort(reverse=True)
    print(math.factorial(b))
    print(' '.join((''.join(p) for p in hoan_vi)))

import math
def sinhhoanvi(a, l, r, res):
    if l == r:
        res.append(''.join(a))
    else:
        for i in range(l, r + 1):
            a[l], a[i] = a[i], a[l]
            sinhhoanvi(a, l + 1, r, res)
            a[l], a[i] = a[i], a[l]
t = int(input())
for j in range(t):
    n = int(input())
    print(math.factorial(n))
    a = [str(i) for i in range(1, n + 1)]
    res = []
    sinhhoanvi(a, 0, n - 1, res)
    res.sort(reverse = True)
    print(' '.join(res))

def hv(a, l, r, res):

        res.append(''.join(map(str, a)))

            a[l], a[i] = a[i], a[l]
            hv(a, l + 1, r, res)
            a[l], a[i] = a[i], a[l]

from itertools import permutations
import math
t = int(input())
for _ in range(t):
    n = int(input())
    arr = list(range(1,n+1))
    perms = ["".join(map(str,p))  for p in permutations(arr)]
    perms.sort(reverse = True)
    print(math.factorial(n))
    print(" ".join(perms))
